.TH "HTMLIMAGEELEMENT.ISMAP" "3JS" "November 17, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLImageElement.isMap \- HTMLImageElement: isMap property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]isMap\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R] interface indicates that the image is part
of a \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image_map#Server-side
server\-side map
.UE \c
\&.
If so, the coordinates where the user clicked on the image are sent to
the server.
It reflects the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element\(cqs \f[CR]ismap\f[R] content
attribute.
This attribute is allowed only if the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element is a
descendant of an \f[CR]<a>\f[R] element with a valid \f[CR]href\f[R]
attribute.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] For accessibility reasons, you should generally avoid
using server\-side image maps, as they require the use of a mouse.
Use a client\-side image map instead.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A Boolean value which is \f[CR]true\f[R] if the image is being used for
a server\-side image map; otherwise, the value is \f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH USAGE NOTES
When an image marked as being part of a server\-side image map is
clicked, the browser constructs the string \(lq?x,y\(rq, where x and y
indicate the coordinates at which the mouse was clicked as offsets from
the top\-left corner of the image, specified in CSS pixels.
.PP
The browser then fetches that URL from the server and displays or
downloads it depending on the value of the \f[CR]download\f[R]
attribute.
.PP
Unlike server\-side image maps, client\-side image maps don\(cqt cause
the \f[CR]<img>\f[R] element to adopt interactive content mode.
